title: Nick Reiner Pleads Not Guilty To Parents' Murders As Prosecutors Weigh Death Penalty | 10 News
description: Nick Reiner has pleaded not guilty to the murders of his parents, Rob Reiner and Michele Reiner, who were fatally stabbed inside their West Los Angeles home last year.  The 32-year-old faces two counts of first-degree murder over the December 14 killings.  Prosecutors are considering whether to seek the death penalty if the case proceeds to trial.  Reiner remains behind bars without bail, with a preliminary hearing scheduled for April 29. title: Blizzard Dumps 30cm Of Snow Across US North-East, NYC Declares State Of Emergency | 10 News
description: A powerful blizzard has dumped more than 30 centimetres of snow across the US north-east, stopping travel and forcing the cancellation of around 5,700 flights.  Roads and rail services were shut down, thousands lost power and schools closed as officials urged residents to stay off the streets.  In New York City, more than 38 centimetres fell in Central Park, with another 13 to 15 centimetres forecast before the storm eases.  New York City Mayor Zohran Mamdani declared a state of emergency, warning residents to stay home as heavy snow continues across parts of the region.
